column17:
[DAOstar](https://daostar.org) is the standards body of the DAO ecosystem, composed of over 80 key organizations in the space including every major DAO framework, a large number of DAO tooling companies, and many major DAOs. We're the IETF of DAOs.

We authored and maintain [EIP-4824 / DAOIP-2: Common Interfaces for DAOs](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4824), along with [many other standards](https://github.com/metagov/daostar/tree/main/DAOIPs) already published and in development. You can participate in the [working groups](https://daostar.one/), or start contributing to our [discussion forum](https://github.com/metagov/daostar/discussions).

Help us shape the future of DAOs!

In short, we've been working on:

1.  DAOstar Regulatory Interoperability\xa0(a.k.a. Millennium Falcon), led by Captain Joni Pirovich, focused on defining a regulatory API / interface so that we can get legal benefits, especially limited liability status. This will eventually transition into a working group on tax standards.
2.  DAOstar Grants Management, working with Gitcoin, OpenQ, DaoLens, Station, kycDAO, Solana, and others to define a common grants system standard for DAOs and other Web3 entities (e.g. L1 foundations), timed with the recent Gitcoin protocol launch.
3.  DAOstar SAFE for DAOs, basically creating a smart contract version of the YC SAFE using fancy game theory to verify equivalence.
4.  DAOstar Governor Ecosystem Standards\xa0with Tally, OpenZeppelin, ScopeLift, Nouns, Joke DAO.
5.  DAOstar Attestations\xa0(a.k.a. Voyager), led by Mendes at Avenue, focused on building an interoperable (and minimal!) attestations system for DAOs and DAO tooling, compatible with SBTs, DIDs, verifiable credentials, and other attestation tooling.
6.  DAOstar Delegations, working with folks at Karma, Agora, Tally, Uniswap, and Optimism to define a delegate registry and standard schemas for delegation!
7.  More infrastructure development, including a new frontend, better indexing, multichain support (i.e. we already have Cosmos DAOs getting indexed), deeper indexing (so displaying not just the URIs but also retaining the membership rolls), and historical data.
8.  Actual community management led by\xa0[@amanwithwings](https://github.com/amanwithwings)\xa0and\xa0[@unfriendlyamendment](https://github.com/unfriendlyamendment)\xa0!"}, {'questionId': 10, 'question': "Anything else you'd like to share about your project, previous work, or other project affiliations? column17:
DeCartography is a computational oracle that aims to provide
multidimensional ties such as Social Diversity and Social Distance
between wallet addresses based on their on-chain activity in
the Ethereum network. The goal is to provide a near-objective social
graph using the notion of common knowledge "wisdom of the crowd"
by iterating subjective human evaluations of each address against a
community-defined cluster. Our current demo includes data from
the latest gitcoin round (Round 15).

column17: Stackly is a simple DCA (Dollar-Cost Averaging) tool that utilizes the CoW (Conditional Order Workflow) Protocol to place TWAP (Time-Weighted Average Price) orders. It allows users to stack their favorite cryptocurrencies at any frequency they choose, such as hourly, daily, weekly, or monthly. By following a DCA strategy, users can reduce their exposure to short-term price fluctuations and potentially build a more stable and profitable long-term portfolio.

column17:
FiatConnect makes it easy for web3 wallets and dapps to integrate with multiple on/off ramps with a standardized API, removing the pain of achieving global on/off ramp coverage.

We're building as a set of open source tools, including a detailed [API specification](https://github.com/fiatconnect/specification), reference [SDK implementation](https://github.com/fiatconnect/fiatconnect-sdk), and [validation tooling](https://github.com/fiatconnect/validate).

There is a set of on/off ramp providers that support FiatConnect compliant APIs and provide coverage across North America, South America, Europe, Asia, and Africa.

ðŸŒ±ï»¿ Gardens is a 1Hive initiative to create a template for public communities to coordinate shared resources from the bottom-up, taking the best lessons learned from the 1Hive community and allowing any DAO to implement them in a plug-and-play fashion. 

With Gardens, anyone can set up a DAO in minutes, leveraging Conviction Voting, a Community Covenant, and the Celeste arbitration protocol, while also getting the network effects of joining a community of quickly blooming Gardens DAOs.

column17:
useWeb3 is a developer platform to explore, learn and starting building in the Web3 space. A curated overview of the best resources, tutorials, opportunities, grants, 'good first' issues, starter kits, etc. Anything to get you started.

Features 
- a curated overview of the best learning resources, courses, tutorials, code challenges, etc.
- starter kits, tools to start building
- grants, jobs bounties and earning opportunities
- a 'good first' issues explorer to make your first contributions 
- gas tracker
- academy to earn ZK certifications

column17:
This project is enabling people to search for crypto related jobs and increase crypto ecosystem adoption. The project is about collecting and aggregating vacancies directly from various Web3 companies daily and to provide better overview of Web3 landscape. And completely open source!

The project delivers following features:
- collect open positions directly from actual carriers web sites daily
- collect open positions history per company
- enable simple way to search for a specific position by location or business area via table or a list view

column16: pRoots:   genomic data protocol on plasmid for bridging synbio and web3 for desci ecosystem
column17: pRoots is a decentralized science project on building genomic data protocol focusing on plasmid collaboration, exchange, and knowledge creation. This project is funded from [GR15](https://bounties.gitcoin.co/grants/7445/proots-empower-people-to-store-share-annotate-and). Due to the supporter, we can keep pushing the boundary and try to bridge web3 and Synbio by solving information, and collaboration gaps in key elements such as a plasmid.

column17:
Stake Together is an Ethereum staking protocol that enables the power of decentralized collaboration to benefit communities. 

By leveraging cutting-edge DVT technology, community members can stake Ethereum and allocate rewards to their communities. 

This innovative protocol promotes growth, knowledge-sharing, and social impact, as content creators take on the role of educators, teaching newcomers about Ethereum staking and introducing them to the world of web3. 

Our mission with Stake Together is to create a sustainable, inclusive, and socially impactful business model that allows everyone to thrive in the rapidly evolving web3 landscape.

column16: Taho - Open Source and Community Owned Wallet
column17:
Help fund the development of the first open source and community owned decentralized Web3 wallet! All funds raised by this grant will flow to the community multisig wallet, which you can verify on Gnosis.

If you haven't tried the wallet yet, what are you waiting for? Download the extension at taho.xyz.

Are you a dev or an open source enthusiast? Come over to our Github repo and help us make the magic happen!

Find out more about what we're building on our blog, and make sure to join the community on Discord!

Building â˜† Tools â˜† for the Defi Community

Small independent team creating tools to help Defi Users quantify the risks and the rewards of providing Liquidity to various Defi Protocols.

All our tools are Open-Source and free to use.

Development updates:

Q2 2021
Creation of Uniswap V3 Simulator --> https://defi-lab.xyz/uniswapv3simulator
Creation of Polygon Network dashboard (Gas fee calculator) ---> https://defi-lab.xyz/polygonnow

Q3/Q4 2021
Backtester Functionality added to Uniswap V3 Simulator

Q1/Q2 2022
Open source Uniswap V3 Backtester functionality --> https://github.com/DefiLab-xyz/uniswap-v3-backtest
Creation of Perpetual V2 Simulator --> https://defi-lab.xyz/perpetualsimulator

Q4 2022
Support different Network (Optimism, Arbitrum, Polygon, Celo)
Backtester improvements

column16: Fusion â€“ Open Source Web3 Icon Set
column17:
Making web3 more beautiful, fast, and open through great iconography.

I believe the best way to bring personality and performance to websites and products is through great design and technology. My goal is to make that process simple, by offering an intuitive and robust collection of open source icons. By using fusion, you can integrate icons seamlessly and however you prefer.

Fusion for vue and react @ NPM
https://www.npmjs.com/package/@fusion-icons/vue
https://www.npmjs.com/package/@fusion-icons/react

Fusion is available as Figma Community File 
https://www.figma.com/community/file/986322091716622056

column17: Rave Names is a web3 username platform with our multichain domain service in development. Rave Names strives to abstract away the biggest roadblock in crypto adoption long addresses, for both users and developers. ZeroPool is blockchain agnostic privacy engine. Our solution is build on zkSNARKs. We research and create privacy technologies under fully opensource license and you can use it in your products.

EVM, Substrate, NEAR implementations are available and live on testnet, and WAVES implementation is coming soon.

What is under the hood:

* Fawkes-crypto / Groth16 / Plonk /Poseidon / * Solidity / Typescript / Angular / NestJs / RxJS

Done:
* Support of PLONK 2022 Q1

Future Plans:
* Implementing lightweight recursive prover with delegated zero knowledge proving based on Sangria (https://zkresear.ch/t/running-sangria-final-proof-in-shielded-mode-on-untrusted-3rd-party-prover/133) Q2 2023
* ZkZkRollup Q2-Q3 2023

', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'Carbon credits are crucial for incentivizing emissions reductions, promoting clean technologies, and supporting conservation efforts to combat climate change and biodiversity collapse. However they currently lack robust safeguards in monitoring, reporting, and verification (MRV), leading to inaccuracies and inefficiencies. A recent Guardian article highlighted that more than 90% of credits are deemed worthless due to incorrect baselines.

GainForest aims to assist nature-based conservation and climate-focused projects by designing a planetary computer with open and transparent analysis capabilities. The planetary computer is a cutting-edge computational platform that harnesses the power of decentralized science and open AI models and data to deliver continuous improvements and provide projects with AI-driven analysis based on their submitted data. This includes processing and analyzing wildlife camera and drone imagery, offering insights into the state of forests, animal detections, and other critical ecological parameters. By leveraging advanced technologies and promoting open collaboration, the planetary computer empowers climate NGOs to make data-driven decisions and implement effective conservation and climate action initiatives, without the need of AI expertise.

We are proud to have onboarded several key partners onto our platform, including the government of Paraguay, the Bhutan Ecological Society, the Kayapo Indigenous Project, and local youth-led NGOs in the Philippines, among others. These organizations are already benefitting from our algorithms and transparency dashboard (https://maps.gainforest.app). '}, {'questionId': 9, 'question': 'Please share any new updates or milestones from the prior season.', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': 'We are excited to share several significant updates since GR15, showcasing our ongoing commitment to advancing environmental conservation and climate action:

We have introduced "Measure-to-Earn," a groundbreaking DeSci protocol that enables local communities in the Philippines to earn income from data measurements while ensuring transparent tracking of donations to individual members. Within just two days, this initiative has made a significant impact on 40 community members, leading to the planting of 300 seedlings and the measurement of 300 trees. Learn more: https://tinyurl.com/gainforest-sbs-boston

We sponsored two climate negotiators from the Global South to attend COP27 in Egypt, providing them with training and advocating for a loss and damage fund and equitable rights. Learn more: https://blog.gainforest.earth/cop27

To date, we have measured 37,000 individual trees and supported projects in the Philippines, Bhutan, and Paraguay by providing drones, wildlife cameras, and training for local communities. Learn more: https://gainforest.app/science

We recently launched the "Green Globe Hub," an interactive, web-based visualization platform displaying real-time environmental data and project updates from around the world. Learn more: https://blog.gainforest.earth/green-globe

We are in the final stages of developing an advanced large language model to analyze carbon credit documents and a tree cover model to predict tree crown delineation using drone imagery. Stay tuned for more updates on our Discord channel: https://discord.gg/SsQhjPDasg

We are thrilled to announce that over 20 new projects, including those from ReFi and beyond, have joined our platform, leveraging our transparency dashboard for in-depth analysis. One of our local partners successfully secured funding for their tree planting efforts, with the donor citing GainForest's transparency dashboard as a critical factor in their decision. Learn more: https://gainforest.app/overview/24

In addition, we are honored to be among the final 15 teams competing in the global $10M XPRIZE Rainforest competition, taking place in Singapore this June. This event will provide an incredible opportunity for us to test our biodiversity-monitoring algorithms alongside talented teams from around the globe. Learn more: https://biodivx.org'}, {'questionId': 10, 'question': "Anything else you'd like to share about your project, previous work, or other project affiliations? column16: Faster API for resolving ENS names and avatars for web3 projects
column17:
I've integrated ENS resolving into several projects now (both my own and as a contributor/collaborator), but found the standard approach of querying ENS contracts directly to be quite slow for most use cases, and can quickly eat up Alchemy/Infura node resources if you're not careful.

To help with this, I built an incredibly fast API (thanks to Cloudflare's edge caching) for resolving and reverse-resolving ENS names and addresses and avatars (30-50ms with a warm cache).

API docs are here: https://ensideas.com/about

And open source code here: https://github.com/holic/ens-ideas

Examples:
https://api.ensideas.com/ens/resolve/0xc9c022fcfebe730710ae93ca9247c5ec9d9236d0
https://api.ensideas.com/ens/resolve/frolic.eth

column16: Esteroids - a community .eth websites search engine
column17:
Esteroids (esteroids.eth) is a community search engine for .eth websites! 

While the .eth web previously offered a variety of innovative .eth websites, it lacked the tools to collect, explore and showcase these websites to the community.

We, therefore, launched esteroids.eth in April 2021 in order to give .eth websites a dedicated search engine. 

We see the .eth web as a fundamental piece of future Ethereum, and a community search engine as a fundamental infrastructure for this web.

(Months)', 'type': 'number', 'hidden': False, 'answer': '22'}, {'questionId': 8, 'question': 'Describe your project in a few paragraphs (ideally including a problem statement, solution, roadmap, and timeline for implementation)', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'How many new ideas never see the light of day or receive the attention they deserve because of our current scientific publishing landscape? Can we create new organizational structures that promote greater creativity and diversity of thought in science? Can people outside of academia make valuable contributions if given the proper platform and support?

Seeds of Science is an experimental publishing platform that aims to provide some preliminary answers to these questions. We overcome many of the issues that plague scientific publishing by subverting some of the more restrictive norms and conventions used in traditional journals â€” speculation and early-stage ideas are not only allowed but encouraged, peer review is fast and decentralized (no opaque gatekeeping by a small group of editors or months-long waits for decisions), authors are free to write in whatever style or format best suits their ideas (as long as the ideas are original, scientifically useful, and clearly expressed), and we pay authors (or send their payment to a charity of their choosing) instead of charging them exorbitant publication fees.

Our primary criterion can be distilled into one question - does the article contain original ideas or analysis that have the potential to advance science? Peer review is conducted through community-based voting and commenting by our diverse network of "gardeners" (free to join, open to all with demonstrated scientific interest/expertise). Another unique feature of SoS worth noting is that comments from gardeners which usefully critique or extend the ideas in the article are published along with the main text. 

In the short term, our goal is to grow our gardener community and continue publishing innovative articles that might not find a home in more traditional journals. Over the long term, our pie-in-the-sky dream is to leverage the journal and gardener community to build a new kind of scientific organization, something like a rogue university/scientific society coordinates research activities of a more exploratory and unconventional nature while also providing support to independent researchers.'}, {'questionId': 9, 'question': 'How does your project support the mission or goals of DeSci?', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'The publication process at traditional scientific journals has become highly exclusionary to all but the most senior academic researchers. Publication fees, increasingly cumbersome submission processes, and excessively critical review processes have made it tremendously difficult for independent researchers, graduate students, and undergraduates to publish anything but the most conservative and conventional articles. Seeds of Science does away with all of these features that tend to exclude researchers by having simple submission and revision processes and being open to non-traditional articles written in more informal or experimental styles (and no publication fees). This allows us to serve as a platform where researchers can publish early-stage ideas and receive feedback on them from a diverse community of scientists - a critical function that is not adequately supported in the current centralized scientific landscape. 
We also support the goals of DeSci through our community-based review process in which our â€œgardenersâ€ vote and comment on manuscripts and have their comments published along with the manuscript. Our decentralized review process stands in contrast to the peer review process at most journals in which 2-3 in-depth reviews are provided by anonymous experts. While this review process has its strengths, it is less appropriate for more speculative or exploratory work which can benefit from a wider range of perspectives and a more charitable style of feedback aimed at extending and improving ideas. Our review process also provides an opportunity for people outside of senior academic positions (anyone with demonstrated scientific interest/expertise can become a gardener) to participate in a review process and, crucially, receive credit for doing so by having their comments published. In addition, we offer qualifying gardeners a dedicated biography page and publish a document with all of their peer review comments (assigned a DOI, searchable in academic databases).
'}, {'questionId': 10, 'question': 'Describe how funds from the grants program will be used for your project.', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': 'Operating costs - (paying authors, CrossRef registration for DOIs, website hosting, Twitter Blue)

Hiring a marketing/outreach assistant - promoting awareness of SoS through online marketing, interfacing with universities and other scientific organizations, and recruiting authors/gardeners. '}, {'questionId': 11, 'question': 'If you participated in past grant rounds (i.e. DeSci GR15) using a different project payout wallet address, please share it here.', 'type': 'address', 'hidden': True, 'encryptedAnswer': {'ciphertext': 'qpl8e/3XvqEWb8CaE2fL7oAeKfnreTcAI5UXa3E6YjU=', 'encryptedSymmetricKey': ''}}, {'questionId': 12, 'question': 'If this project participated in past grant rounds, please share any new updates or milestones since the last round.', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': ''}, {'questionId': 13, 'question': 'Is there any other information you would like to share about your project, previous work, other project affiliations, or potential conflicts of interest? Health data is not decentralized and clinical trials remain quite archaic, plus technical and legal challenges. As humans, we gather a large amount of health data and do not utilize it properly for the community's good. We record it with smart devices, and this data is taken by big corporations.

AxonHealth is also addressing the problem of a lack of engagement and motivation among individuals to take control of their health goals. Traditional approaches to health and wellness often focus on reactive solutions and overlook the importance of a â€œpatient-centricâ€ approach, where the individual is empowered to take proactive measures for their own well-being. Furthermore, the current healthcare system is fragmented, with individuals having limited access to their health data, making it very difficult to track their progress and make informed decisions about their health or alert them of potential health issues.  

Advances in healthtech such as wearable devices, mobile health apps and health sensors allow continuous, passive, non-invasive, accurate measurement of daily activity levels, heart rate, sleep patterns, mental health and other health metrics. Combined with data mining, biomarkers, and AI/ML analysis we can provide users with personalized insights and recommendations as well as over time perform research at a larger population based level to improve our algorithms and prediction models. AxonHealth also provides community support and mentorship which aligns with this mission of community empowered health. The use of blockchain technology allows for decentralised storage of health data, giving individuals â€œdata sovereigntyâ€, and allowing them to monetize their data and participate in contests and studies for rewards without compromising privacy and security of their sensitive data.

AxonDAO will build its web3 health data platform with experienced clinical practitioners and skilled DAO members to gamify health data, find a market and value for the data, while conservatively following all laws. Our mission to the bring value personal data back to the user, and liberate people from their data being used against them, when it could help solve the biggest problems.

(or anything not covered elsewhere in this application that you feel is relevant to share)', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False, 'answer': "=========
THE NEED 
=========
Agricultural companies that need to optimize irrigation and fertilization practices, and reduce water waste and pollution.
Municipalities that need to manage water supply and demand, monitor infrastructure performance, and respond to emergencies.
Industrial companies that need to track water usage and quality, and comply with regulations.
NGOs and research institutions that need to study and monitor water resources, and support sustainable development

============
THE MARKET
============

According to a report by MarketsandMarkets, the global market for water management systems is expected to grow from $21.7 billion in 2020 to $29.9 billion by 2025, at a CAGR of 6.6%. 
The European market for smart water management is expected to grow at a CAGR of 14.4% from 2020 to 2027, according to a report by Allied Market Research.
A report by the European Environment Agency (EEA) states that water scarcity is a significant issue in many regions of Europe, with increasing competition for water resources due to population growth, climate change, and other factors.
The EU's Water Framework Directive (WFD) sets out a framework for the protection and sustainable use of water resources in Europe, including requirements for member states to monitor and report on water quality and availability. 
A survey by the European Commission found that 68% of Europeans are concerned about water pollution and scarcity, and 82% believe that more action is needed to protect water resources. 


============================
OUR COMPETITIVE ADVANTAGE
============================
Our solution has several advantages over existing products in the market:
More comprehensive and integrated, covering the entire water management cycle from data collection to decision-making.
More accurate and reliable, thanks to our use of advanced technologies such as machine learning and remote sensing.
More scalable and customizable, thanks to our cloud-based infrastructure and modular design.
More user-friendly and accessible, thanks to our intuitive interface and training materials
"}, {'questionId': 14, 'question': 'Does 50% of your team reflect the diversity of the community your project serves with a particular emphasis on including women, Black, Indigenous, and People of Color (BIPoC), individuals with disabilities, and members of the LGBTQ+ community?', 'type': 'multiple-choice', 'hidden': True, 'encryptedAnswer': {'ciphertext': 'qXz5UIDAMPers3JUJ+XF9DyYdauy7tp5EnHMFqVxkcg=', 'encryptedSymmetricKey': ''}}]

column16: Nowhere Publishing (NFT books with open access content)
column17:
Nowhere Books publishes and sells high quality NFT books. Each NFT book features a unique cover designed by an artist, and attaches an openly assessable content licensed in Creative Commons.

Targeted impacts:
- find an alternative, working business model for book publishing which is a quickly shrinking market especially in Asia.

- break the walled garden by offering an alternative form of ebook which has no DRM (digital right management) and can be read on any device

- store book content immutably on decentralized solution

column17:
ATX DAO is a social organization based in Austin, Texas. Our goal is to unite Austin's crypto communities, enable artists and local businesses to participate in the crypto ecosystem, and educate the government about the benefits of Web3. 

As a democratic network of developers, artists, and crypto professionals, the DAO provides expertise to local and state government, organizes social events to onboard new web3 users, and helps the best minds in blockchain connect, coordinate, and collaborate in service of public goods.

', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': "Since January 2021, ATX DAO's community footprint has brought a number of diverse events to the Austin web3 scene. 


We have co-hosted many educational seminars, with topics ranging from data privacy in blockchain, government policy, investing in crypto markets and trends among traditional finance. Our educational events are free and open to the public, consistently bringing in 40-80 attendees. During SXSW 2023, ATX DAO hosted a concert featuring local Austin musical talent alongside digital artists, welcoming over 1,000 people throughout the event. We also co-hosted a workshop for Rust developers via partnership with Near Protocol, as well as a Hackathon in June 2022 to offer blockchain developers an educational opportunity.


ATX DAO has a strong presence in the local community. In June 2022, we sponsored a local artist to paint a large mural which was converted into a 3D NFT to memorialize the art and allow owners to participate in an ongoing art fund. In December 2022, ATX DAO introduced a charitable giving fund via partnership with EnDAOment to create a source for members to offer contributions to local charities (Mobile Loaves & Fishes, Upbring, and Austin Pets Alive). ATX DAO recently launched a job board to help connect talent seekers with top skills of our endorsed community members.


Alongside the University of Texas McCombs Business School, we hosted the first-ever web3 pitch competition with 73 applicants and offered $160k in prizes to winning projects. 


On the policy side, we have hosted two formal events of 100+ attendees each, bringing together government officials with blockchain professionals and community members. Our members have researched legal challenges associated with DAO formation and offered two formal testimonies in the Texas Congress. We have publicly advocated against projects that we believed were the result of bad actors and were successful in communicating those concerns to public officials.

column17:
Dot.alert() is a knowledgebase that provides practical guidelines for managing Web3 assets safely and mitigating Web3 platforms' risks.

Dot.alert() proposes ELI5 articles targeted at entry users that can be understood by a non-crypto audience. All content is open-source and accessible in a multilingual context: it can be translated in-browser and leveraged by creators to produce educational materials in audio-visual formats.

Dot.alert() is a collaborative platform for sharing community expertise, with content populated by contributors with specialist knowledge in an array of fields, including Web3 wallets, protocols, infrastructure, technologies, and regulatory developments.

', 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': True, 'answer': 'Dot.alert() is a knowledgebase that can be used as a reference for exploring Web3 ecosystems because the ELI5 articles are targeted at entry users and can be understood by a non-crypto audience.  The content is open-source: it can be translated in-browser and re-used by Web3 creators; and the platform has been designed as a collaborative space for sharing community expertise and onboarding contributors with specialist knowledge.

Dot.alert() has published over 30 articles covering Web3 infrastructure projects (i.e wallets, explorers, user-friendly platforms, etc.), transactions (i.e on-chain governance, staking, slot auctions, token swaps, etc.), and use cases (i.e Privacy, Identity, Crowdfunding, Security, Infrastructure, etc.). 
The platform also gives the wider crypto community the opportunity to engage with its content and publications through a monthly quiz which tests participantsâ€™ knowledge of blockchain and Web3 technologies. 

Dot.alert() has been growing a diverse audience over the past six months through social media campaigns across Twitter, Reddit, and Discord; as well as SEO audits which aim to improve the visibility and findability of its content. During Q1 2023, the platform aggregated over 3,000 views and attracted more than 300 visitors from over 60 different countries covering all areas of the world, including Africa, Southeast Asia, and the Middle East. 

Despite being a relatively new project, Dot.alert() seeks to maintain the highest standards in terms of accessibility of information, diversity of contributors, and multilingual community outreach. The platform regularly collects feedback from visitors through quarterly user surveys and provides the general audience with pathways to steady employment and/or career development within the Web3 industry.

Built Different is an African Web3 startup community and DAO
started in Harare, Zimbabwe. We connect founders, developers
and enthusiasts, build a shared and inclusive community around a
more open, honest and decentralized internet in Africa.
We are working to support local developers to build tools that can bridge the divide and help more Africans participate in Web3 in new and novel ways built around the African context.

column17:
Hello,

I have created a series of Ethereum mainnet and testnet staking how-to guides for staking on Ubuntu.

- Configuring Withdrawal Credentials

- Ethereum Consensus Clients: Lighthouse, Nimbus, Prysm, Teku, and Lodestar

- Ethereum Execution Clients: Besu, Erigon, Geth, and Nethermind

These guides are intended for new/intermediate users, and are hopefully a reasonable and pleasant onboarding vehicle for newcomers to the Ethereum staking community.

Upcoming work: 

- Migration guides to encourage client diversity

Your support is appreciated <3

Somer

See [here](https://github.com/SomerEsat/ethereum-staking-guides) for guide listing and change logs.

column17:
ETH KIPU is an organization dedicated to supporting the Ethereum ecosystem in Latin America. Co-created by Latam Community Leaders aligned with Ethereum values.

We contribute to creating communities and support them in their growth, promote education about Ethereum, foster the creation of public goods on Ethereum and organize the main Latin American Ethereum event every year: [ETH Latam](https://twitter.com/ethlatam)

Our mission is to educate the Latam community about the Ethereum ecosystem using sustainable formats. The content will be open source and free.

[Our handbook](https://ethkipu.notion.site/English-6ec09df094514c47bb6faeba8837f38d)

Everyday people are being attacked and scammed in Web3. 

We started Boring Security to educate people on what they can do to remain safe in this ever-evolving space. 

We provide free classes, resources, tools, and other informational material to the community so that they can prevent themselves from becoming the next victim.

column17: Burning Sissy Valley is a 1-day QTPOC (Queer, Trans People of Color) pride event. The Event consists of QTPOC focused workshops (one including web3 and finance), networking, performers and ends with a dance party. The objective of the event is to build community, provide resources, and highlight QTPOC community members and artists.

CreatorDAO is building a platform to allow anything to be commissioned (e.g. Image, Audio, 3D, Lore, Animation, etc). From vision to imagination to creation, spreading seeds with unlimited potential into the metaverse.

We believe the NFTs space is entering the next stage, where original NFTs holders need new creativities and stories for their NFTs. For every BAYC, every Azuki, there could be an independent brand or even a specific metaverse.

And we are a DAO making it possible.

column17:
Defi Wars is an educational analytics site with a mission to democratize access to crypto data. 

## Some of our top features include: 
* tracking top governance token holders (such as veCRV, vlCVX, etc.)
* tracking pegs of liquid wrappers (such as cvxCRV, etc.)
* tracking LSDs of Ethereum, Avalanche, and more
* tracking pegs of LSDs such as stETH


## We're currently tracking:
* 40 protocol wars
* 13 blockchains
* 50+ liquid wrappers
* 150+ projects


**We have huge plans in the future to expand the data and features we offer and need your help!**

We are Andino, a community of web3 developers and creators. We promote education and entrepreneurship in emerging technologies such as blockchain.

We carry out events such as meetups, workshops and hackathons, collaborating with educational entities such as universities to onboard university students to start their career as web3 creators.

column17:
Definomics Labs is an educational hub that aims to migrate financial talent from web2 to web3 and empower/professionalize Latin American talent in the DeFi & Tokenomics space.

Definomics Labs was born in The Merge (September 2022), We've already have +7 IRL meetups and more than 15 virtual meetings.

Given our goal to professionalize the DeFi and Tokenomics space, we collaborate with universities, high schools, and microfinance institutions.

Greenpill is an exploration of regenerative cryptoeconomics.  How can we rotate capital and talent from regen to degen? 

I've done 105 episodes about this subject.  Some favorites:
1. Daniel Schmatenberger
2. Yancey Stricler
3. Optimism
4. DAO Drops 
5. Protocol Guild
6. Austin Griffith


   You can checkout the podcast at https://greenpill.party/

column17: Advantage Blockchain is laser focused on educating the next billion blockchain users. We curate and distribute multiple forms of educational materials such as quarterly market reports, bi-weekly newsletters, 1-on-1 tutoring sessions, and in-person events when possible. Being in the crypto industry since 2016 has taught us how valuable the buidl years are for so many projects and companies in the space so we plan to use funding to explore new educational routes as mainstream adoption picks up steam!

SEED Latam is a non-profit organization dedicated to promoting, supporting, and accompanying web3 communities in Latin America. We have been working since 2020, and many communities and projects have been born within our community, making us a multiplier of builders and educators in the space.

We bring together educators, developers, researchers, artists, entrepreneurs, students, and enthusiasts who build and promote knowledge and critical thinking about Ethereum. Our goal is to raise awareness and knowledge about web3 in Latin America and empower the leaders of the future

As such, MantleSwap can benefit the Mantle network ecosystem in several ways, including:

Increased adoption: As a user-friendly and cost-effective DEX built on the Mantle network, MantleSwap can attract more users to the network, leading to increased adoption and usage.

Enhanced liquidity: By providing a platform for users to trade tokens on the Mantle network, MantleSwap can help increase liquidity on the network, which can improve the overall health and efficiency of the ecosystem.

Lower transaction fees: The Mantle network aims to reduce transaction fees and increase scalability, and MantleSwap can help achieve this goal by providing a cost-effective way for users to trade tokens without incurring high gas fees.

Improved user experience: MantleSwap can enhance the user experience on the Mantle network by providing an intuitive and user-friendly interface for users to trade tokens. This can help attract more users to the network and improve overall engagement.

Lighthouse is an Ethereum consensus-layer client. We provide a stable, performant and open-source implementation which is relied upon by a significant portion of the Ethereum network.

We're actively engaged in research, specification and implementation. Providing a safe and scalable base-layer is our commitment and passion.

We are now rallying towards the Deneb fork to provide scaling via L2 solutions.

The wagmi team builds TypeScript tooling for Ethereum. Our libraries are used by organizations like ENS, Optimism, Sushi, Foundation, Gitcoin, and Stripe.

* [**wagmi**](https://github.com/wagmi-dev/wagmi) â€” React Hooks for Ethereum
* [**viem**](https://github.com/wagmi-dev/viem) â€”  TypeScript Interface for Ethereum (ethers.js alternative)
* [**ABIType**](https://github.com/wagmi-dev/abitype) â€” Strict TypeScript types for Ethereum ABIs

Your contributions support the entire wagmi project. The funds collected are used to support the core team and compensate significant contributions to the project. Our work is only sustainable thanks to the generous financial backing of our Gitcoin donors.

column17:
Direct funding for the Ethereum maintainers!

A collective of 130 Ethereum core contributors working together to enable commons infra funding that is:

- sourced from the community
- transparent & onchain
- autonomously distributed

Members come from 20 different projects, including developers working on clients (eg. Geth, Lighthouse), researchers (eg. EF Research) and coordination (eg. Ethereum Cat Herders): https://protocol-guild.readthedocs.io/en/latest/9-membership.html

Using independent, existing governance processes (eg. All Core Devs call, Magician's Forum) members help stewards both Ethereum (the network) and the EVM, taking care to consider current needs and how they may evolve.

PADO utilizes interactive zero-knowledge proofs (IZK) and MPC to authenticate users' off-chain data and maintain their privacy via TLS standards. The project is a typical Ethereum infrastructure, because:
1. PADO will open-source all the cryptographic algorithms for Ethereum (and other web3) community developers. They can use the IZK tools to build their own zk-applications with a much more efficient zk-prover compared with zk-SN(T)ARKs. They can also use the related MPC tools (highly optimized garbled circuits and OTs) to build specific private features.
2. PADO will run decentralized nodes to off-chain data attestation services, which can be further integrated with Ethereum attestation service (EAS) to support the abstract attestation layer, and to enhance off-chain data trust and privacy.
3. PADO will also create a simple open-source client software to demonstrate the power of interactive zero-knowledge proofs. IZK relies on primitives like garble circuits and oblivious transfers to compose a general-purpose computation logic, towards the underlying boolean circuits. IZK shares the prover efficiency and low memory cost, which is a perfect choice for building zk applications on the end-user devices (a zk-prover can be executed within several megabytes, which is feasible on a browser extension or mobile app), and maintaining a zk-verifier service online. As the initial plan, we consider to aggregate and prove the userâ€™s CEX assets for any on-chain protocols."}, {'questionId': 9, 'question': "If you've participated in past grant rounds, please share any new updates or milestones from the prior months", 'type': 'paragraph', 'hidden': False}, {'questionId': 10, 'question': "Anything else you'd like to share about your project, previous work, or other project affiliations?
